Harry Tate https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harry_Tate 0 Ronald Macdonald Hutchison (4 July 1872 - 14 February 1940), professionally known as Harry Tate, was an English comedian who performed both in the music halls and in films. Tate worked for Henry Tate Sons, Sugar Refiners before going on the stage, and took his stage name from them.
